# Branch Naming Convention

Use prefixes to clearly indicate the purpose of the branch:

`feat/`    - New feature
`fix/`     - Bug fix
`refactor/`- Code improvement without behavior change
`docs/`    - Documentation
`chore/`   - Project setup, tooling, or maintenance
`test/`    - Adding or updating tests
`style/`   - Code style (formatting, linting, etc.)

example: git checkout -b feat/signup-ui

# Commit Message Convention
`feat:`     - New feature
`fix:`      - Bug fixes
`docs:`     - Documentation changes
`chore:`    - chores
`style:`    - style
`refactor:` - refactor code, no behaviour change
`test:`     - Adding or modifying tests

example: git commit -m `feat: add signup UI with validation`